CHANGES IN VERSION 1.6 (2026-05-02)
-----------------------------------

* Fixed a bug where --rg-tag silently enabled --use-secondary due to a
  missing break in the option parser.

* Fixed a double-free crash when --bedGraph and --bed/--bed-ins were used
  together.

* Fixed the secondary alignments percentage in the text report, which was
  incorrectly computed from single-end read counts.

* Fixed the JSON depth histogram "range" field, which incorrectly reported
  the fragment histogram maximum instead of the depth histogram maximum.

* Fixed the JSON "addn_stats_are_suspect" flag for fragment sizes, which
  was inverted (reported suspect when the histogram tail was empty).

* Fixed genomic coverage undercounting when one read is nested inside
  another (last_end now takes the max of the two endpoints).

* Fixed --bed-ins: the Tn5 forward shift was subtracted from the start
  coordinate instead of added, placing insertions 8 bp upstream.

* Fixed --bed-ins: the first insertion record was missing from output due
  to an off-by-one in the initial buffer endpoint.

* Fixed 1st/99th percentile calculations to use count-based CDF (percentile
  of reads/positions) rather than mass-weighted CDF (percentile of bases).
  Reported values for qlen, flen, depth, GC, and MAPQ will change.

* Fixed avg_mapq for mitochondrial/plastid chromosomes: MAPQ=255 reads
  (mapper-reported unavailable) are now excluded from the denominator as
  well as the numerator.

* Fixed invalid JSON output when filenames, titles, or RG tags contained
  backslashes or control characters.

* Fixed --save crashing when the output BAM file could not be created.

* Fixed a stack buffer overflow in BED name parsing (very long name fields).

* Fixed CRAM extension stripping in output filenames (.cram was unreachable).

* Fixed TSS pileup range labels in JSON for even --tss-size values.

CHANGES IN VERSION 1.5 (2025-09-12)
-----------------------------------

* Added read quantification (--quant). This outputs a TSV of read
  counts, with peaks as rows and samples as columns. The peaks can
  be provided via --peaks. Quantification can be at the insertion
  level via --quant-ins.

* Fixed a couple of bugs with --bed options.

CHANGES IN VERSION 1.4 (2025-08-29)
-----------------------------------

* Added BED output (--bed). The behaviour of this output is similar
  to the default behaviour of `bedtools bamtobed`. Additionally, the
  BED can contain the Tn5 insertion coordinates instead of the
  original alignment coordinates by adding the --bed-ins option.

* Fixed typos & formatting errors in output reports

* More --bedGraph bugfixes

* Fix compilation of included zlib library with newer LLVM versions

CHANGES IN VERSION 1.3 (2025-05-04)
-----------------------------------

* Added the ability to filter reads using alternate SAM tags instead of
  read groups (RG) via --rg-tag. 

* Fixed some bugs in the --bedGraph implementation.

CHANGES IN VERSION 1.2 (2025-05-03)
-----------------------------------

* Added bedGraph output (--bedGraph). The behaviour of the output pileup
  is similar to the pileup created by the --tss option, with the ability
  to either make a pileup from the exact read coordinates or centered
  around resized 5-prime coordinates.

CHANGES IN VERSION 1.1 (2024-06-13)
-----------------------------------

* Added --strict flag: Use strict filtering parameters from manuscript

* Overlapping ranges provided to --tss are now removed to prevent imbalanced
  pileups due to reads only being counted for the first overlapping range
  even if multiple overlapping ranges exist

* Fixed a bug with read overlap detection for --tss option

